com.intel.icecp.core.management

Interface Channels

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MockChannels

    public interface Channels
    Interface for creating and tracking channels; uses registered ChannelProviders. Use: 

    
 Channels channels = new Channels();
 channels.register("ndn", new NdnChannelProvider());
 channels.openChannel(URI.create("ndn:/..."), SomeMessage.class, ...);

      • openChannel

        <T extends Message> Channel<T> openChannel(URI uri,
                                           Class<T> messageType,
                                           Persistence persistence,
                                           Metadata... metadata)
                                    throws ChannelLifetimeException
        (Non-generic) Open an implementation of a channel with the given metadata; what non-included metadata will default to is implementation-specific. Use this method for non-generic classes such as String.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the Message type
        Parameters:
        uri - the unique identifier for the channel, including the scheme to open it (e.g. 'ndn:').
        messageType - a Class instance of the Message
        persistence - the declared caching/retrieval policy for messages on the channel
        metadata - a list of metadata
        Returns:
        the opened channel
        Throws:
        ChannelLifetimeException - if the channel cannot be opened

        messageType - a Token instance of the Message
